content.thinking:
The replay-btn has a fixed 26x26px size. I need to update it to be at least 44x44px touch target. Rather than changing the visual appearance, I should change the width/height to 44px. The SVG inside is 13px, so the button will look a bit larger, but still compact.

Actually, I'm already overriding it at the bottom of the CSS with:
```css
.replay-btn {
  padding: 9px;
  width: 44px;
  height: 44px;
}
```

This will override the 26x26 size since it comes later in the CSS. 

So the icon stays at 13px while the clickable button expands to 44x44px, which gives plenty of padding around it.

